    {
      "id": "5a93c517_c0c56e5c",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/resources/config/pe/pap.conf",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "Jorge, It's for pdp not drools I guess. So why are you changing it to 4?\nBTW I will change it to the range function of helm tomorrow (as I have got it working) to generate this string dynamically based on number of replicas so that manual changes are not required in case of scale in/out.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2763,
        "name": "Mahendra Raghuwanshi",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "mahendra.raghuwanshi@amdocs.com",
        "username": "mahendrr"
      },
      "updated": "2018-05-15 13:42:25.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_a08dc232",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/resources/config/pe/pap.conf",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "Mahendra, I was experimenting with the scaling options.  For example:\n\nhelm upgrade -i dev local/onap --namespace onap --set policy.pdp.replicaCount=3\n\nThe new instance will be generated with dev-pdp-3 ..\n\nThis allows for those instances to be accepted by the white listing mechanism on the PAP (allowed PDP-Xs to communicated with have to be whitelisted a priori), accepted and synchronized with the policies.   See tests at:\n\nhttps://wiki.onap.org/display/DW/Scalability%2C+Resiliency+and+Manageability\n\nSo, in theory, this allows a dynamic scaling of +2 (in addition to the 2 from initialization).   Otherwise, with scaling on the fly, those PDP-X will be rejected.\n\nMakes sense?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2018-05-15 13:50:02.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5a93c517_c0c56e5c",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5a93c517_a0bb82c2",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/policy/resources/config/pe/pap.conf",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "As I said, It can be taken care of using range function of helm.\nPlease take an example from consul/charts/consul-server/templates/statefulset.yaml which I did today. It can be generated at runtime based on number of replicas.\nBut if you can't convert it to the range function then I will put a patch tomorrow on this review itself and will be just changing this logic, rest looks ok anyways (Of course if it could wait till tomorrow).",
      "author": {
